Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil (large pot for 4 servings).
Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{4%oz},
half the @Soy Sauce{2%tbsp}, half the @Sesame Oil{1%tbsp}, and half the
@Rice Wine Vinegar{5%tsp} (all the soy sauce, all the sesame oil, and all
the vinegar for 4).

Once water is boiling, add @Vermicelli Noodles{3.5%oz} to #pot{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{4-6%minutes}. Drain.

Open package of @Skinless Dark Meat Chicken{10%oz}(diced) and drain off any
excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and @Shredded Carrots{4%oz} in an even layer. Season with
@Garlic Powder{1%tsp}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until carrots are browned and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Add sauce to pan; stir to combine.

Transfer drained noodles to pan with chicken mixture; toss to combine.

Divide noodles and chicken between shallow bowls. Garnish with scallion greens
and @Peanuts{1/2%oz}. Drizzle with as much @Sriracha{2%tsp} as you like. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.